Introduction :

  • This datasets came from reports flights in the United States, including carriers, arrival and departure delays, and reasons for delays, from 1987 to 2008.
  • Data source from United States Department of Transportation - Bureau of transportation Statistics

  1. Are there certain destination or arrival cities that are home to more cancellations?
  2. what is the change in delay rate over years
  3. What are the preferred times for flights to occur?Are there any changes over multiple years?

what is the change in delay rate over years?¶

A flight delay is when an airline flight takes off and/or lands later than its scheduled time. The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) considers a flight to be delayed when it is 15 minutes later than its scheduled time. A cancellation occurs when the airline does not operate the flight at all for a certain reason.
source : https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flight_cancellation_and_delay#:~:text=A%20flight%20delay%20is%20when,all%20for%20a%20certain%20reason.

#create colleration materix by using heat map and matrix to figure out what is the most factor affecting on flight delays
from string import ascii_letters

sb.set_style(style="white")

# Compute the correlation matrix
corr =delays.corr()

# Generate a mask for the upper triangle
#mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(corr, dtype=bool))

# Set up the matplotlib figure
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(11, 9))

# Generate a custom diverging colormap
cmap = sb.diverging_palette(230, 20, as_cmap=True)

# Draw the heatmap with the mask and correct aspect ratio
sb.heatmap(corr,  cmap=cmap, vmax=.3, center=0,annot=True,
            square=True, linewidths=.5, cbar_kws={"shrink": .5});

Almost the correlation between all variable is very small and we can't get a clear vision if there is one variable effect to another so we will using another approach in order to try to depict flight

Conclusion for preferred time to fly:¶

  • March, January and April have highest flight number
  • Friday has highest number of flights
  • Most flights occurred daily from 6:AM to 7:00PM
